                                 አምላክ፡ … </q> The note mentions the church of ʾabuna Libānos as the
                              owner of the Ms. Besides, the names of <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12067WaldaKrestosAnbasat">qaysa gabaz Walda
                                 Krǝstos</persName> and <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12072WaldaAmlakAnbasat">
                                 <t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="office">makʷannǝn
                                    ‘ruler’</t:roleName> Walda ʾAmlāk</persName> are mentioned.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Corrections written interlineally: <locus target="#8ra">8ra</locus>, 49ra, 79va, 100ra, 117va, 118rb, 119rb.
 </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"> - The word እገሌ, “so-and-so” and some other words in the
                           section of Antiphons are marked by thin lines above and below throughout
                           the Ms.
 </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">- A recent ownership note in pencil mentioning
                              ʾAnbasat ʾabuna Libānos as the owner of the Ms.: <locus target="#120v">120v</locus>.</desc>
 
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"> - Pen trial extended by a plea for God to make the pen
                           good: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>. </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Notes in the upper margins referring to the
                              content of the Ms.: fols. 16vb, 27rb, 35vb, 38va, 47vb, 50rb, 52vb.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc type="findingAid"> -
                              Coloured stripes of cloth have been inserted in the outer margin of
                              fols. 13, 18, 71, 92.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
